    {
      "id": "85740a9f-25f3-4991-9d84-1793d4b87f86",
      "type": "description",
      "value": {
        "latex": "On considère l'équation $(E)~:~(z-1)^n-(z+1)^n=0$ où $n$ est un entier naturel supérieur ou\négal à $2$ donné.",
        "html": "<p>On considère l’équation <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\((E)~:~(z-1)^n-(z+1)^n=0\\)</span> où <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(n\\)</span> est un entier naturel supérieur ou égal\nà <span class=\"math inline\">\\(2\\)</span> donné.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "8d3fa994-c2e4-4280-b686-7a794051fb97",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Montrer que les solutions de $(E)$ sont imaginaires pures.",
        "html": "<p>Montrer que les solutions de <span class=\"math inline\">\\((E)\\)</span>\nsont imaginaires pures.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "e300f4df-2111-4347-a86f-fc1e2c9d3aa2",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Soit $z\\in\\Cc$. Soient $M$, $A$ et $B$ les points d'affixes resectives $z$, $1$ et $-1$.\n\n$$\\begin{align*}\nz\\;\\mbox{solution\nde}\\;(E)&\\Rightarrow(z-1)^n=(z+1)^n\\Rightarrow|(z-1)^n|=|(z+1)^n|\\Rightarrow|z-1|^n=|z+1|^n\n\\Rightarrow|z-1|=|z+1|\\\\\n &\\Rightarrow AM=BM\\Rightarrow M\\in\\mbox{med}[AB]\\Rightarrow M\\in(Oy)\\Rightarrow z\\in i\\Rr.\n\\end{align*}$$",
        "html": "<p>Soit <span class=\"math inline\">\\(z\\in\\Cc\\)</span>. Soient <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(M\\)</span>, <span class=\"math inline\">\\(A\\)</span>\net <span class=\"math inline\">\\(B\\)</span> les points d’affixes\nresectives <span class=\"math inline\">\\(z\\)</span>, <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(1\\)</span> et <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(-1\\)</span>.</p>\n<p><span class=\"math display\">\\[\\begin{align*}\nz\\;\\mbox{solution\nde}\\;(E)&amp;\\Rightarrow(z-1)^n=(z+1)^n\\Rightarrow|(z-1)^n|=|(z+1)^n|\\Rightarrow|z-1|^n=|z+1|^n\n\\Rightarrow|z-1|=|z+1|\\\\\n&amp;\\Rightarrow AM=BM\\Rightarrow M\\in\\mbox{med}[AB]\\Rightarrow\nM\\in(Oy)\\Rightarrow z\\in i\\Rr.\n\\end{align*}\\]</span></p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "35b9abf6-8d0b-49db-8abe-a29fdea97b1e",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Montrer que les solutions de $(E)$ sont deux à deux opposées.",
        "html": "<p>Montrer que les solutions de <span class=\"math inline\">\\((E)\\)</span>\nsont deux à deux opposées.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "309d2c07-8214-4555-88c1-6774a90dd3b9",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Soit $z\\in\\Cc$.\n\n$$(-z-1)^n-(-z+1)^n=(-1)^n((z+1)^n-(z-1)^n)=-(-1)^n((z-1)^n-(z+1)^n).$$\nPar suite,\n\n$$z\\;\\mbox{solution de}\\;(E)\\Leftrightarrow(z-1)^n-(z+1)^n=0\\Leftrightarrow(-z-1)^n-(-z+1)^n=0\\Leftrightarrow-z\\;\\mbox{solution de}\\;(E).$$",
        "html": "<p>Soit <span class=\"math inline\">\\(z\\in\\Cc\\)</span>.</p>\n<p><span\nclass=\"math display\">\\[(-z-1)^n-(-z+1)^n=(-1)^n((z+1)^n-(z-1)^n)=-(-1)^n((z-1)^n-(z+1)^n).\\]</span>\nPar suite,</p>\n<p><span class=\"math display\">\\[z\\;\\mbox{solution\nde}\\;(E)\\Leftrightarrow(z-1)^n-(z+1)^n=0\\Leftrightarrow(-z-1)^n-(-z+1)^n=0\\Leftrightarrow-z\\;\\mbox{solution\nde}\\;(E).\\]</span></p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "a783b2b6-a19b-42c6-adc0-1ca513af76c5",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Résoudre $(E)$.",
        "html": "<p>Résoudre <span class=\"math inline\">\\((E)\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "dd1d859e-1627-494a-a834-14a2c00526f5",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Soit $z\\in\\Cc$.\n$$\\begin{align*}\nz\\;\\mbox{solution de}\\;(E)&\\Leftrightarrow(z-1)^n=(z+1)^n\\Leftrightarrow\\exists k\\in\\llbracket0,n-1\\rrbracket/\\;z-1=e^{2ik\\pi/n}(z+1)\\\\\n&\\Leftrightarrow\\exists k\\in\\llbracket1,n-1\\rrbracket/\\;z=-\\frac{e^{2ik\\pi/n}+1}{e^{2ik\\pi/n}-1}\n\\Leftrightarrow\\exists k\\in\\llbracket1,n-1\\rrbracket/\\;z=-\\frac{e^{ik\\pi/n}+e^{-ik\\pi/n}}{e^{ik\\pi/n}-e^{-ik\\pi/n}}\\\\\n&\\Leftrightarrow\\exists k\\in\\llbracket1,n-1\\rrbracket/\\;z=-\\frac{2\\cos\\frac{k\\pi}{n}}{2i\\sin\\frac{k\\pi}{n}}\n\\Leftrightarrow\\exists k\\in\\llbracket1,n-1\\rrbracket/\\;z=i\\cotan\\frac{k\\pi}{n}\n\\end{align*}$$",
        "html": "<p>Soit <span class=\"math inline\">\\(z\\in\\Cc\\)</span>. <span\nclass=\"math display\">\\[\\begin{align*}\nz\\;\\mbox{solution\nde}\\;(E)&amp;\\Leftrightarrow(z-1)^n=(z+1)^n\\Leftrightarrow\\exists\nk\\in\\llbracket0,n-1\\rrbracket/\\;z-1=e^{2ik\\pi/n}(z+1)\\\\\n&amp;\\Leftrightarrow\\exists\nk\\in\\llbracket1,n-1\\rrbracket/\\;z=-\\frac{e^{2ik\\pi/n}+1}{e^{2ik\\pi/n}-1}\n\\Leftrightarrow\\exists\nk\\in\\llbracket1,n-1\\rrbracket/\\;z=-\\frac{e^{ik\\pi/n}+e^{-ik\\pi/n}}{e^{ik\\pi/n}-e^{-ik\\pi/n}}\\\\\n&amp;\\Leftrightarrow\\exists\nk\\in\\llbracket1,n-1\\rrbracket/\\;z=-\\frac{2\\cos\\frac{k\\pi}{n}}{2i\\sin\\frac{k\\pi}{n}}\n\\Leftrightarrow\\exists\nk\\in\\llbracket1,n-1\\rrbracket/\\;z=i\\cotan\\frac{k\\pi}{n}\n\\end{align*}\\]</span></p>\n"
      }
    }
  ],
